abstract: "This repository proposes Universal Task Language (UTL), a structural intermediate language between human intent and autonomous software construction. UTL represents tasks, objectives, requirements, workflows, and plans independently of natural language, programming languages, frameworks, and implementation details. The project further introduces the Task All-in-one Graph, Universal Naming and Typing (UNT), All-in-one CallingGraph-based naming and typing, and the UTL-UNT dual semantic infrastructure."
